   {:e #blake3 "e9179ab77c96dfe1523dc57917611608e091a619f4b334775168d7051be72996" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Sync/frontier propagation has zero dedicated tests. Multi-store merge relies on frontier comparison to determine what datoms to exchange. If frontier comparison is wrong, merges could silently drop data. RATIONALE: INV-MERGE-001 (set union completeness), INV-STORE-004 (frontier semantics). Frontier is implicitly tested in merge tests but edge cases (empty frontier, single-datom frontier, frontier with retractions) are not explicitly covered. APPROACH: (1) Test: two stores with disjoint datom sets, merge, verify union is complete. (2) Test: two stores with overlapping datoms, merge, verify no duplicates. (3) Test: store A has retraction that store B doesn't, merge, verify retraction propagates. (4) Test: empty store merges with populated store — frontier is complete. (5) Test: frontier comparison with concurrent transactions (same entity, different attributes). ACCEPTANCE: (A) 5 dedicated frontier tests pass. (B) Edge case: empty frontier merge produces correct result. (C) Edge case: retraction-only merge propagates correctly. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/store.rs or new tests/frontier_sync.rs" :op :assert}
